<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#F0DCA0">Originally posted by Ragon der Magier on 05-10-2002 12:03 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=20 COLS=75 WRAP="VIRTUAL">  [QUOTE]Originally posted by Dorien Karei:
[i](edit)- I almost forgot, a bug I discovered while playing the demo further, if you end up being a dolt like me, accidently forgetting to switch from the lock picking skill option and make an attempt to use a special move, in this case that spin attack move on a target, you instead begin trying to lock pick the monster's nose, the problem is, when you realize you have the wrong skill set and back off to change it, you can't attack back, or use an other skill until you click on a monster again to stop attempting to pick lock...aswell, something that could be of a big help that the game could use, having item labels that appear when you put your cursor over an item on the ground to pick it up, should always be seen on items that are sitting on the ground, since you can't see through walls to see items that may have dropped, you have to wave the cursor around to locate any hidden items you may want, persistant labels would make it easier to find those items hiding behind walls.[/i][/QUOTE]

[b]That´s funny as i experienced the very same problem, just exactly the other way round!  :][/b]
Was when i tried to achieve s.th. on an object via the right mouse button, as if a kind of context menu could open. All that because it didn´t react on left moouse click of course!  ;)
To make a long story short, i triggered the [i]special move[/i] in an completely inadequate situation.
Yet, i´m still undecided if the Larians should better exclude the possibility of accidently executing a [i]360[/i] when not in [i]combat mode[/i]. Will have to sort out between being in [i]combat/normal mode[/i] and the common use of [i]skills[/i] in either realm. Maybe they should get assigned to each separated vicinity, so that you can use combat related only in the according mode and vice versa... somehow!?  :confused:  :rolleyes:
What i tried was harvesting some herbs, and when it didn´t immediately go into my inventory, despite it got highlighted on mouseover, not even on second try when i had it dedicatedly open for that purpose, there was not much more left to come to my mind but attempting standard windows procedures  :( (aye, that sentence sounds a bit spooky, doesn´t it!?  ;)  >:)).
I had expected some special method to cut the herbs from the ground perhaps, and therefore tried the skill-activating right button.
Now i gathered from various other topics that apparently you just need to care for those plants when if you have an empty flask with you, as the action on the herb with it will then turn it immediately into a potion!
I find this to be a rather unfortunate and clumsy restriction of the game. :(

To your second part, however, i could tell you that i myself have been told by lar in person that it´s the ALT key, baby!  ;)
Just hold it down and it is said all items on the screen as well as special "hot spots" like doors to become marked by text pop-ups!  :)

NBye,
Ragon


